      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>drained potatoes</strong>,<strong> ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>nigella seeds</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until crisp and golden – these are your <strong>masala potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
