    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Rub a little <strong>vegetable oil </strong>onto a baking tray (this stops the fish from sticking!)</p><p>Add the <strong>breaded</strong> <strong>fish fingers </strong>to the oiled tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 8-10 min or until the fish is golden, crispy and cooked through – these are your <strong>Indian-spiced fish fingers</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
